	(411,1,'2020-05-21 09:47:02','2020-05-21 08:47:02','<h2>INTRODUCTION:</h2>\n\nWe are looking for an experienced Area Service Engineer to work on all types of electronic security equipment. This role will be suited to somebody who has previously worked on CCTV, Access Control, EAS Equipment, Integrated Software Solutions Intruder alarms or similar security equipment.\n\nThis is a field-based role covering a regional area. Whilst the successful applicants will be based in this area in order to meet aggressive SLA’s working outside this area may be required.\n\n<h2><b>MAIN PURPOSE OF ROLE:</b></h2>\n\nAmberstone Security Limited a leading electronic technology solutions provider is looking for a talented Area Service Engineer join its team in the UK. The function of the Area Service Engineer is to act as the mobile field service engineer on assigned open jobs &amp; work in collaboration with senior engineering staff members, Customer Service Centre &amp; Logistics to resolve customer affecting technical issues in a timely fashion in order to maintain maximum customer satisfaction second to none.\n\nThe Area Service Engineer troubleshoots &amp; maintains an extensive variety of products &amp; equipment. Trains customers, identifies, analyses &amp; repairs product failures, orders &amp; replaces parts as needed.\n\nThe employment offer to the successful candidate will be subject to passing a security clearance check, in line with industry standards.\n<h2><b>KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:</b></h2>\n<ul class="styled-list">\n 	<li>Ability to work independently &amp; exceed customer expectations &amp; organisational objectives.</li>\n 	<li>Diagnose system problems in minimal time &amp; make accurate repairs.</li>\n 	<li>Highly effective interpersonal communication skills</li>\n 	<li>Handle customers in a professional manner during difficult high-pressure situations.</li>\n 	<li>Excellent follow-through in meeting commitments, deadlines &amp; resolving escalations.</li>\n 	<li>Excellent time management &amp; organizational skills to maximize productivity.</li>\n 	<li>Excellent driving &amp; safety record operating company vehicles</li>\n 	<li>Make recommendations for improving the service, reliability &amp; performance of our equipment.</li>\n 	<li>Resolve technical issues by seeking timely advice or assistance from technical support when necessary.</li>\n 	<li>Maintain accurate stock holding &amp; inventory</li>\n 	<li>Completion &amp; submission of all relative documentation in a timely manner ensuring its accuracy.</li>\n 	<li>Follow up on formal training with self-training</li>\n 	<li>Maintain high levels of technical expertise &amp; behaviours through continuous improvement</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>PERSON SPECIFICATION:</h2>\n<h3>Qualifications, Training &amp; Experience:</h3>\n<ul class="styled-list>\n 	<li>Must have either a recognised qualification or historic “on the Job” experience in the electronic security field.</li>\n 	<li>Valid driver’s licence, with a good driving record</li>\n 	<li>Good working knowledge of PC hardware &amp; be PC literate</li>\n 	<li>Experience in a similar customer-facing environment working to achieve customer service levels</li>\n 	<li>Commercial awareness is desirable</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Required Skills &amp; Competencies:</h3>\n<ul class="styled-list>\n 	<li>Highly effective interpersonal communication skills</li>\n 	<li>Understand critical linkages between own work &amp; other areas of the business.</li>\n 	<li>Strong customer-facing skills</li>\n 	<li>Highly self-motivated &amp; self-directed.</li>\n 	<li>Communication, Team-working &amp; Interpersonal Skills</li>\n 	<li>Brings new ideas to the team</li>\n 	<li>Strong analytical skills</li>\n 	<li>Must be a team player</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nTo apply for this role, please email your CV and any other supporting information to enquiries@amberstone.co.uk','Service Engineers','','inherit','closed','closed','','53-autosave-v1','','','2020-05-21 09:47:02','2020-05-21 08:47:02','',53,'http://amberstone/news/53-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(412,1,'2020-05-21 09:52:23','2020-05-21 08:52:23','<h2>INTRODUCTION:</h2>\n\nWe are looking for an experienced Installation Engineer to work on all types of electronic security equipment installations. This role will be ideally suited to somebody who has previously worked on CCTV, Access Control, Intruder alarms or similar security equipment.\nThis is a field-based role covering UK North. Whilst the successful applicants will be based in this area in order to meet aggressive SLA’s, the area of coverage is not limited to UK North and traveling further afield is to be expected.\n\n\n<h2>MAIN PURPOSE OF ROLE:</h2>\n\nAmberstone Security Limited a leading electronic technology solutions provider is looking for a talented individual to join its team in the UK. The function of the role is to act as the installation Engineer on assigned projects, open jobs &amp; work in collaboration with senior engineering staff members in order to maintain maximum customer satisfaction.\n\nThe Installation Engineer will deliver installation projects from concept to completion by working with the engineering team and project support. The role focus will be on client satisfaction, seamless delivery, and commercial awareness.\n\nThe employment offer to the successful candidate will be subject to passing a security clearance check, in line with industry standards.\n\n\n\n<h2>KEY DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</h2> \n\n<b>Other duties may be assigned.</b>\n\n1) Project Compliance – Amberstone is a NSI Gold accredited installer so all installations must achieve this standard, it is the duty of the Project Manager/Engineer to ensure that this standard is achieved on all Installations, also ensure all projects comply with the requirements for health &amp; safety, environmental regulations and general duty of care for both employees and customers.\n\n2) Site Meetings – Coordinate, manage and contribute effectively to all site meetings as and when necessary or requested.\n\n3) Adherence to policy – Adheres to company policy in relation to Health &amp; Safety and Equal\nOpportunities and complies with all policies and procedures as laid out in the current company staff handbook.\n\n4) Mission, Core Values &amp; Competencies-Embrace the company’s core values &amp; principles in order to achieve the overall mission of the organisation. Take personal responsibility for own career development by continually assessing and adjusting personal performance and behaviour against the criteria laid out in the organisations competency framework.\n<div></div>\n\n\n<h2>PERSON SPECIFICATION:</h2>\n<h3>Qualifications, Training &amp; Experience:</h3>\n<ul class="styled-list">\n 	<li>Must have either a recognised qualification or historic “on the Job” experience in the electronic security field or similar environment.</li>\n 	<li>Valid driver’s licence, with a good driving record</li>\n 	<li>Good working knowledge of site working and associated H&amp;S procedures</li>\n 	<li>Experience in a similar customer-facing environment working to achieve customer service levels</li>\n 	<li>Commercial awareness is desirable</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<strong>REQUIRED SKILLS &amp; COMPETENCIES:</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Highly effective interpersonal communication skills</li>\n 	<li>Understand critical linkages between own work &amp; other areas of the business.</li>\n 	<li>Strong customer-facing skills</li>\n 	<li>Highly self-motivated &amp; self-directed.</li>\n 	<li>Communication, team-working &amp; Interpersonal Skills</li>\n 	<li>Bring new ideas to the team</li>\n 	<li>Must be a team player</li>\n</ul>\n\nTo apply for this role, please email your CV and any other supporting information to enquiries@amberstone.co.uk','Installation Enginner','','inherit','closed','closed','','54-autosave-v1','','','2020-05-21 09:52:23','2020-05-21 08:52:23','',54,'http://amberstone/news/54-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
